&lt;h1&gt;Sister/Charge Nurse&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;1 year Secondment Opportunity&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Are you an experienced nurse with an interest in acute Medical nursing and keen to develop your leadership and management skills?&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking to recruit an existing band 6 or a band 5 who is passionate about patient care and motivated to develop as a band 6 and work alongside the management team on D7.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;D7 is a busy acute medical general medicine ward. The patient group is complex, presenting with complex vascular problems and all types of acute general medical conditions.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are dedicated to providing the optimum care for this group of patients and work as an integral part of a multidisciplinary team to enable us to achieve this. As a key member of the team you will play a pivotal role in ensuring the delivery of optimal quality care and safety.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;As a ward sister you would be expected to support the nursing team in delivering high quality care to patients, you will act as a positive role model and as well as supporting the team clinically you will also deliver on operational demands.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We can offer a very supportive team environment and in house courses to develop for personal and professional progression. If you feel you may be the person for this role or ready to take the next step in your career please contact us to discuss.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Informal visits prior to interview are welcome, please contact Sefora Melo on 02392 286000 EXT 4185.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date 12/11/2020&lt;/p&gt;
